**Archived Containment Procedures:** ENOCH.AIC is to monitor global security feeds for reports of individuals matching SCP-7376's description.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Prior to the discoveries of SCP-7376-B, SCP-7376-C, and SCP-7376-Ω, SCP-7376-A was the only anomaly categorized under the SCP-7376 designation.[[/span]] In the event of a confirmed match, [[[/task-forces#psi-13 | Mobile Task Force Psi-13 (“Witch Hunters”)]]] are to be dispatched to subdue and capture SCP-7376. Standard procedures for the containment of a Karcist[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Karcist:** Honorific given to the spiritual and secular leaders of the Nälkä. Karcists are biologically immortal and possess extremely dangerous carnomantic abilities.[[/span]] are to be used until SCP-7376's anomalous abilities are better understood, at which point they will be altered accordingly.

**Special Containment Procedures:** SCP-7376-A is to be terminated within 67 seconds of emergence from SCP-7376-B-2.

To facilitate SCP-7376-A termination cycles, a containment enclosure—henceforth referred to as the Primary Containment Zone (PCZ)—has been built within SCP-7376-B's central chamber, walling off SCP-7376-B-2 from the rest of the complex. Personnel are not allowed to enter the PCZ during an Awakening Event; all termination apparatus within the PCZ are to be operated remotely by members of Stationary Task Force Alpha-73 ("Cain-Do Attitude") from Containment Area-25B's control room.

[[div class="term_box"]]

= **Termination Apparatus**

----

* Electric Deterrence System
* Omnidirectional Flame Units
* COGNITOBURST[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**COGNITOBURST:** Experimental memetic weaponry designed to simultaneously transmit cognitohazardous information along six different vectors: sight, sound, smell, taste, touch, and telepathy.[[/span]]
* High-Pressure Industrial Water Cannons (Hydrochloric Acid)
* Plasma Projectors[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Plasma Projector:** Directed energy paraweapon originating from the Cold War.[[/span]]
* Congelation Cannons[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Congelation Cannons:** Containment apparatus originally developed for [[[SCP-5657]]]. High-pressure foam spray that, upon contact, hardens to 3000 kilograms per cubic meter in .002 seconds.[[/span]]

[[/div]]

In the event that SCP-7376-A is successfully terminated but does not expire within 45 seconds, STF Alpha-73 is to alter containment procedures with the goal of increasing termination efficacy & efficiency. Efforts are to be made to prevent SCP-7376-A from predicting or adapting to methods of termination.

If any damage occurs to the PCZ during a termination cycle, STF Alpha-73 is to perform all necessary repairs during SCP-7376-A's dormant phase.

In the event that SCP-7376-A escapes the PCZ, Mobile Task Force Alpha-76 ("Ready, Willing, and Abel") is to utilize corrosive/incendiary weaponry to terminate the anomaly before it can breach containment. If a breach occurs, all surviving members of MTF Alpha-76 are to coordinate with MTF Psi-13 to locate and terminate SCP-7376-A.

SCP-7376-A may not, under any circumstances, be brought into contact with anomalies that expand, augment, improve, or otherwise significantly alter human consciousness/cognition.

__EDIT:__ As of O5 Council's 05/15/2003 decision, SCP-7376-A has provisionally been assigned the secondary class Flor Galana[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Flor Galana:** Item partially contains itself and/or other anomalies, but cannot be fully contained for logistical and/or ethical reasons.[[/span]] and its containment procedures are to be heavily revised.

**Description:** SCP-7376-A is a humanoid anomaly with the appearance of a 30-35 year old man of Middle Eastern descent. Roughly 75% of its skin has been tattooed with thaumaturgic symbols closely associated with long-range carnomancy.

In the event that SCP-7376-A dies, its body will fully disintegrate within 45-89 seconds. After a dormant phase lasting between 3 days and 2 months, SCP-7376-A will begin an Awakening Event, growing a new body within SCP-7376-B-2 over the course of 13 hours. Upon the Awakening Event's conclusion, SCP-7376-A will exit SCP-7376-B-2 covered in a thin layer of amniotic fluid and dressed in simplistic clothing made of its own skin.

SCP-7376-A is a carnomancer with abilities equivalent to that of a Karcist. It possesses extremely fine control over its body's cells, being able to manipulate skin/bone/muscle/etc. for a variety of offensive and defensive purposes. This, in combination with SCP-7376-A's innumerable years of combat experience and extreme hostility towards any form of imprisonment, has made continuous containment extremely challenging.

SCP-7376-A does, however, possess three critical weaknesses:

1. SCP-7376-A's carnomantic abilities are notably weakened in the first 67 seconds after a completed Awakening Event. Should SCP-7376-A continue to be alive after this period has ended, the likelihood of it escaping the PCZ becomes almost certain.

2. SCP-7376-A is either unwilling or unable to use carnomancy to manipulate the organic tissue of other living things, not even to form a Halkost.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Halkost:** Collective term for anomalous organic entities created and controlled by skilled carnomancers.[[/span]] This is a crucial limitation, as the ability to generate anomalous life has always been a force multiplier in conflicts involving the Nälkä.

3. SCP-7376-A appears to require a certain degree of conscious thought to use the full extent of its carnomantic abilities. As such, using COGNITOBURST to disable or hamper SCP-7376-A's actions has been critical to containment efforts. In the event that SCP-7376-A discovers a way to subvert or avoid COGNITOBURST's effects, the likelihood of continued containment success is predicted to drop by at least 70%.

**Addendum 7376-A-1: Association with the Nälkä**

SCP-7376-A's role in human history is difficult to determine. Many of its (theorized) appearances are attributed under different names and subject to countless years of mythologizing. Reports of individuals matching SCP-7376-A's description have cropped up in nearly every known major war (in addition to over 20 large-scale natural disasters). When mapping out a timeline of SCP-7376-A activity, no discernible pattern has yet been found. SCP-7376-A seems to, at completely random intervals, go into seclusion for irregular lengths of time, after which it involves itself in events that invariably lead to massive loss of life. It is unknown if SCP-7376-A's presence has a causal relationship with these cases of mass death or if SCP-7376-A actively seeks them out.

Only one historical period has been verified to have involved SCP-7376-A: the Daevite slave rebellion and the subsequent rise of the Kalmaktama Empire.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Kalmaktama Empire:** A Nälkän empire that rose to prominence in the "golden age" of the Nälkä.[[/span]] Nälkän religious texts and records almost universally refer to SCP-7376-A as Võlutaar Hevel,[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Võlutaar:** Honorific given to a Karcist's advisor. Most Võlutaar are female, to the extent that the word is synonymous with "wise woman".[[/span]] a "warrior-prince" who came to aid the Nälkä in a time of great need.

Most Nälkä cultural groups consider SCP-7376-A to be the most notable Võlutaar in Nälkän history, believing that it was the only Võlutaar to directly advise Grand Karcist Ion himself. That being said, SCP-7376-A's role within Nälkä culture is not analogous to that of a Klavigar; SCP-7376-A appears to be more of a historical figure than a spiritual one.

Nälkä cultural groups generally believe that SCP-7376-A died shortly before or after Grand Karcist Ion's disappearance. In the latter case, the prevailing belief is that SCP-7376-A was killed in Kalmaktama's war with the Mehkanite Empire. In the former case, it is believed that SCP-7376-A sacrificed its life to slay Ab-Leshal, a leviathan spawned by one of Yaldabaoth's Archons.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Ab-Leshal roughly translates to //"a sky-shaped dream"// or //"a flesh-shaped ocean"//.[[/span]] As few mentions of Ab-Leshal have been found outside accounts of this battle, very little is known about this entity (if it ever existed to begin with).

To view a full list of historical events with a theorized connection to SCP-7376-A and/or all known Nälkä texts that involve SCP-7376-A, contact Department of History liaison Ajla Hall.

**Addendum 7376-A-2: Project Pandora**

In the mid-to-late 1890s, the American Secure Containment Initiative (ASCI) began the Omega-7 Initiative (otherwise known as "Project Pandora"), a research program with the stated goal of weaponizing anomalies for use in the United States military.

Exceedingly little is known about Omega-7, as all unredacted files documenting Omega-7 and personnel involved in the project were lost when its base of operations went dark on 10/15/1899. All remaining Omega-7 documentation has been extensively redacted, as per ASCI's then-policy of information suppression. The following information has been deemed irretrievable:

[[include component:image-block
| name=Bowe.png
| caption=Henry Bowe
ASCI Director 1878-1904
| width=200px
| align=right]]

* The date Omega-7 was founded.
* The anomalies used by Omega-7.
* The location of the Omega-7 facility.
* The research produced by Omega-7.
* Omega-7's budget.
* The identities of Omega-7 staff.

One fact about Omega-7, however, has been determined with near-certainty. On 10/08/1899, one week before Omega-7 lost contact with the rest of the ASCI, word was received that SCP-7376-A had been brought into containment and was being transported to the Omega-7 facility.

Only one copy of SCP-7376-A's ASCI documentation has been recovered.

