**Special Containment Procedures:** To increase the likelihood of SCP-7376-Ω remaining in its current state, the processes associated with SCP-7376-A's Awakening Events must not be interfered with.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Dormi:** Item is currently in a dormant or inactive state.[[/span]]

In the event that SCP-7376-Ω becomes active, the anomaly is to be neutralized by detonating the ██ thaumonuclear[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Thaumonuclear:** Nuclear technology that has been enhanced by thaumaturgy.[[/span]] warheads planted along its northern ridge. Should SCP-7376-Ω fail to be neutralized, all available Foundation resources are to be diverted towards the immediate evacuation of Earth's population.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Tiamat:** The threat this item poses can only be contained through Veil-breaking action.[[/span]]

**Description:** SCP-7376-Ω is an anomalous gigafauna of undetermined size located directly beneath SCP-7376-B. The Foundation has taken a strict policy of non-interaction with the anomaly, which has prevented detailed research from taking place. This is what is known for certain about SCP-7376-Ω:

* SCP-7376-Ω is in a state of deep dormancy. Its resting heartbeat is currently at 2 beats per day and its body temperature is only a few degrees higher than the surrounding rock.
* SCP-7376-Ω's emergence would, at minimum, lead to the decimation of Eurasia and the irrevocable disruption of Earth's magnetosphere.
* SCP-7376-Ω and SCP-7376-A possess identical DNA.

**Addendum 7376-A-4-1: Interview Log C3**

[[div class="blockquote"]]

**Date:** 04/02/2000

**Interviewed:** SCP-7376-C

**Interviewer:** Dr. Safiya Light //(Director, Tactical Theology)//

----

**SCP-7376-C:** I didn't just want to "merely" bring my brother back to life; I wanted to resurrect him in such a way that would save him from ever being killed again. Like a child who hides the evidence of their wrongdoing beneath their bed, I thought undoing my mistake would unmake everything that followed it.

I traveled to the Grand Karcist and when I showed him Hevel's body, I asked him to impart a fragment of what he had given his Karcists, his Klavigar. The carnomantic gift that can mend any wound, press the hands of age backwards.

And he said yes. He didn't even hesitate. I think my brother, in his many years away, had become very important to the Ozi̮rmok--or perhaps Ion saw the wisdom in giving the future king of Edinnu immortality, ensuring that an alliance between nations would be just as enduring. I would not assume to know his motivations.

But something went wrong.

To this day, I do not know why. A Daevite curse or some other malignant magic, perhaps, had interfered with the spell. Or Ion made a mistake somehow, pouring too much of himself into the casting. Or death had changed Hevel on a fundamental level, to such a degree that magic that should've matched his soul perfectly now met it as sodium metal meets a dirty puddle.

Whatever the reason, in the instant that his heart started beating, his body began to grow. And grow. And grow. The carnomancy placed inside him boiled out of control like a cancer. By the time the Great Karcist had realized what was happening, it was too late; there was no taking away a gift he had already given.

Hevel became vast. A landscape of skin and sinew. And in this new body, he could only thrash about in cataclysmic fits. The Grand Karcist would later tell me that while his body had dramatically increased in size, his consciousness had not changed in shape. Hevel's body was too large for his thoughts and he was lost in his own depths.

It was then, when Ion made the temple of Ab-Leshal. He buried Hevel in the earth and placed a living tomb atop him, which wrapped thick roots around his brainstem to rock him into an endless dream... all in the hope that one day, against all odds, he'd find his way back to the surface.

And he did... many, //many// years later.

That's what he is. A waking dreamer. The Hevel people know is a puppet. A human-shaped vessel for his human-shaped consciousness. An avatar he experiences the world through. Whenever he dies, his true body simply grows a new one once his mind resurfaces.

**Dr. Light:** Did Hevel ever forgive you?

**SCP-7376-C:** No. Dying, being alone in that ocean of a body for centuries, losing our family and the Grand Karcist... all of it changed him. I do not deserve his forgiveness, of course--but he is no longer the kind man I knew.

I don't know what he is, now. Something cruel and callous. A danger to everyone around him. A thing in dire need of containment.

You //will// contain him, won't you?

**Dr. Light:** We always do, Cain.

