[[div class="blockquote"]]

SCP-7376-A's current containment procedures are unsustainable; "Abel" has been getting closer and closer to a breach with each termination cycle we put him through. As he clearly has continuity of memory between incarnations, we've essentially spent hundreds of thousands of dollars to train SCP-7376-A how to fight us. So long as he possesses the ability to grow a new body after death, containment simply isn't feasible--and I'm sure you understand why interfering with his resurrection mechanism would only open up a much larger can of worms.

