**Addendum 7376-A-6: Initial Negotiation**

Due to their familial relationship, SCP-7376-C was requested to perform the initial negotiations with SCP-7376-A regarding its recruitment. SCP-7376-C displayed strong hesitance, but agreed after being informed that, due to the violent nature of its containment, SCP-7376-A would likely assault any individual it did not recognize while inside SCP-7376-B.

[[div class="blockquote"]]

**Date:** 06/07/2003

//[The bulk of the following exchange was performed in an unidentified language, which SCP-7376-C translated from memory shortly afterward.]//

----

//[The PCZ is emptied of all termination apparatus. The only objects in the room are SCP-7376-B-2, set of chairs, and a small table on which a stack of papers has been set. SCP-7376-C sits at the table, facing SCP-7376-B-2. A door has been installed in the wall behind him. A faint organic pulsing sound is audible as the ongoing Awakening Event nears its conclusion.]//

//[The Awakening Event ends; SCP-7376-A stumbles out of SCP-7376-B-2. Its skin has been hardened by carnomancy, giving it an bright red hue. Its limbs are edged with razor-sharp bone. Amniotic fluid steams off of it. SCP-7376-A looks around wildly, evidently ready for a fight and disoriented by the lack of immediate assault. It appears to have not yet consciously registered SCP-7376-C's presence.]//

**SCP-7376-C:** Hello, Hevel.

//[SCP-7376-A visibly startles.]//

**SCP-7376-A:** //You.//

//[SCP-7376-A storms towards SCP-7376-C, looming over him from the other side of the table. SCP-7376-C looks back at it evenly.]//

**SCP-7376-C:** It's been a long time.

**SCP-7376-A:** Not nearly long enough. Why are you here?

**SCP-7376-C:** I've been asked to speak on behalf of the Foundation--

**SCP-7376-A:** Who?

**SCP-7376-C:** Your captors.

**SCP-7376-A:** What, because you just happened to be nearby?

**SCP-7376-C:** They asked me because they're //terrified// of you, Hevel.

**SCP-7376-A:** That's Võlutaar Hevel to you--

**SCP-7376-C:** Fine. They're terrified of you, //Võlutaar Hevel//--

**SCP-7376-A:** Why's that, hm? I have every right to fight back. They are keeping me here //against my will//.

**SCP-7376-C:** You won't be if you simply allow me to--

**SCP-7376-A:** This was you, wasn't it? I can't believe I didn't realize, this sort of meddling has your stench //all over//.

**SCP-7376-C:** That's besides the poin--

**SCP-7376-A:** Told them about me, did you? Spun your tale of woe. You must have, how else could they imprison me so readily? After all, you do. So. Love. To //talk//.

//[SCP-7376-A glances at a PCZ surveillance camera.]//

**SCP-7376-C:** Hevel--

**SCP-7376-A:** //[Russian.]// I wonder, though, did you ever tell them that you had my corpse //cursed//, so that any harm I would inflict on you would instead land upon myself? Did you tell them about the things your scrapyard god's worshipers have done in your name? Or were you too busy spilling //my// secrets to bring up any of your own?

**SCP-7376-C:** //[Russian.]// I have nothing to hide.

//[SCP-7376-A laughs bitterly.]//

**SCP-7376-A:** //[Russian.]// You're right Qayin, it //has// been some time! I don't remember you ever being //funny// before!

**SCP-7376-C:** //[Russian.]// Just—//listen// to me for a moment!

//[SCP-7376-A suddenly bends down to eye level with SCP-7376-C.]//

**SCP-7376-A:** //No.//

//[SCP-7376-A begins walking towards the exit. On the opposite side, MTF Alpha-76 begins preparing for a PCZ breach scenario.]//

**SCP-7376-C:** Grand Karcist Ion would be ashamed to see what you are now.

//[SCP-7376-A stops moving, still faced away from SCP-7376-C.]//

//[Silence.]//

//[In a sudden burst of movement, SCP-7376-A, turns, hurls itself towards SCP-7376-C, grabs him by the scruff of the neck and slams his head into the table, snapping it in two. Papers fly in every direction. In the moment of SCP-7376-C's impact, thin cracks form along the left side of SCP-7376-A's head.]//

//[Though he lacks any wounds, SCP-7376-C crumples to the ground, clutching his head in apparent pain. MTF Alpha-76 nearly intervenes, but halt when SCP-7376-C performs a prearranged gesture indicating that he does not wish for an extraction.]//

**SCP-7376-A:** How. //Dare//. You.

//[SCP-7376-A lifts SCP-7376-C into the air by the lapels of his shirt, its bladed fingers carving into SCP-7376-C's upper torso. SCP-7376-C winces, still unharmed, as long furrows form on SCP-7376-A's own torso.]//

Bastard. Jackal. Waste of fucking flesh. You speak the Ozi̮rmok's name as though you knew him. As though you have any right to speak of him at //all//.

//[SCP-7376-A's grip tightens.]//

//I// knew him. //I// cared for him. And he cared for me, just the same.

You, who took all that away from me, have--have the //audacity// to look upon me now and speak his name? //How dare you.//

**SCP-7376-C:** //[Speaking haltingly, through clenched teeth.]// You are right. I did not know him. But I do know what else he loved. His people.

//[Silence.]//

**SCP-7376-A:** What?

**SCP-7376-C:** //His people//, Võlutaar Hevel. The slaves of the Daeva. The people of Adytum. The Nälkä. //Your// people. What have you done for them. In all these years?

**SCP-7376-A:** //You don't have the right--//

**SCP-7376-C:** You know better than I. How they have been abused. And manipulated. How their skin has been split. //Your people//. While you stand by. And fight your wars. Why?

**SCP-7376-A:** I—I am a warrior. A channel for violence. That is all that is left to me, //you took everything else—//

**SCP-7376-C:** You do nothing for the Nälkä. You close your eyes to their suffering. You //hide//. Because you know to look upon them. Is to look upon what I took from you.

//[SCP-7376-C briefly cries out in pain as SCP-7376-A's fingers tighten further, deepening the gouges in its own chest.]//

But you can no longer afford. To look away. I know it hurts. But you must face it.

//[SCP-7376-C cries out in pain again.]//

**SCP-7376-A:** //Stop. Talking.//

**SCP-7376-C:** The world is changing. Faster than ever. Are you absolutely certain. That your people are prepared. For the days to come?

The Foundation. Their influence is immense. If you fight under their banner. They will help the Nälkä. Protect them. Provide resources. Find ways of preserving your culture. Return artifacts. When they can.

//[Silence.]//

I know. I have no right. To call you my brother. Not anymore. But you still have a family. //Help. Them.//

//[SCP-7376-A abruptly drops SCP-7376-C to the floor. It rolls its shoulders and its wounds start sealing together, spilled blood disintegrating. The edges of bone begin to retract into its skin, which returns to its natural brown hue.]//

**SCP-7376-A:** //[Russian.]// Fine. I will speak to your "Foundation." But I'll need evidence that they're fulfilling their promises. Regular updates. And the deal is off if they try this shit in the future, using you as a representative. I don't want to see you ever again.

//[Silence.]//

**SCP-7376-C:** //[Russian.]// Very well.

[[/div]]

